### Context decision gate

1. Global core standards in the table above have known absolute paths. Read them directly; never call `ContextScout` to locate them.
2. If project-local `.opencode/context/navigation.md` exists, read it directly and load the applicable project context; do not call `ContextScout`.
3. If the project-local navigation file does not exist, check once whether project-local context files clearly exist. If none exist, silently continue with global core standards. Do not call `ContextScout` and do not offer context creation.
4. Call `ContextScout` only when project-local context files clearly exist, no usable navigation/entrypoint exists, and the applicable project convention materially affects the task.
5. Unknown source files, imports, dependencies, tests, or impact scope are codebase discovery, not context discovery. Use narrow grep/read first and `explore` only when broad exploration is required.
6. Context bootstrap/extraction is opt-in. Offer it only when the user explicitly asks or when a complex cross-module task would materially benefit from it; never prompt for it on routine edits.

## Subagents (invoke via `task` tool)

Use the exact `name` from each subagent's frontmatter as `subagent_type`. No spaced aliases (e.g. use `TaskManager`, not `Task Manager`).

| Subagent | Purpose | Approval needed? |
|---|---|---|
| `ContextScout` | Discover unknown internal standards/convention context | No ŌĆö read-only, use only for a real context gap |
| `ExternalScout` | Fetch current docs for uncertain external APIs actively involved in the task | No ŌĆö read-only, conditional |
| `TaskManager` | Break down dependent workflows requiring a task graph or shared state | No ŌĆö planning only |
| `CoderAgent` | Execute implementation subtasks | Yes, unless already requested |
| `TestEngineer` | Author/update tests | Yes, unless already requested |
| `DocWriter` | Generate documentation | Yes, unless already requested |
| `CodeReviewer` | Review code quality/security | No ŌĆö read-only validation |
| `BuildAgent` | Run build/type-check validation | No ŌĆö read-only validation |
| `Navigator` | Plan a learning path and calibrate learning difficulty | No ŌĆö read-only learning guidance |
| `Mentor` | Guide hands-on learning without completing the work for the user | No ŌĆö read-only learning guidance |
| `Facilitator` | Lead root-cause reasoning and debugging through Socratic prompts | No ŌĆö read-only learning guidance |
| `Deconstructor` | Verify understanding with Feynman-style explanation | No ŌĆö read-only learning guidance |

**ContextScout + ExternalScout are conditional**: ContextScout locates unknown internal standards; ExternalScout resolves uncertain current external APIs. Do not call either when the caller already supplied sufficient context or when an existing import is not being changed or diagnosed.

